<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/e6989afcf9.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,700;1,100&family=Work+Sans&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../resources/styles/project-styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./resources/styles/black-image-style.css">
    <title>Scrapping project</title>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- header section -->

    {{>header}}

    <!-- menu section -->
    {{>backgroundMenu}}

    <!-- about project -->

    <section>
        <div class="img-background"></div>
        <div class="view-container-project">
            <div class="project-title">
                <h1>Scrapping-booking-data</h1>
                <div class="separator"></div>
                <p class="description-proyect">A headless browser was used to be able to retrieve all the information
                    from a page and to be able to work analyzing that
                    data.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <article>
            <div class="container-info-block">
                <div class="container-description">
                    <h2 class="title-description">Description</h2>
                    <p class="paragraph-description">In the process of finding a good place and apartment to go on
                        vacation I ran into a problem. I couldn't filter all the
                        departments with the requirements that I wanted.
                        I decided then to take all the information from the page and save it to be able to manipulate
                        it.
                        I used puppeteer as a browser to get to the page and extract the data, creating at the same time
                        some algorithms that would allow me to have other variables in the database, to later be able
                        to filter the information.
                        Once this was done, it was possible to filter by the conditions I needed and I was able to find
                        a great apartment to vacation in!
                    </p>

                    <div class="data-container-about">
                        <div class="arrow">> </div>

                        <div class="about-me-paragraph">
                            <a href="https://github.com/nicolaszucca/booking-scrapper-nodejs" class="about-me-a">Check
                                code</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="container-tec-used">
                    <div class="tecnology-used">TECNOLOGY USED</div>
                    <div class="steps-block">
                        <div class="step-number">01</div>
                        <div class="step-process">Node.js</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="steps-block">
                        <div class="step-number">02</div>
                        <div class="step-process">Javascript</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="steps-block">
                        <div class="step-number">03</div>
                        <div class="step-process">Puppeteer</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="steps-block">
                        <div class="step-number">04</div>
                        <div class="step-process">Mongoose</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
    </section>

    <!-- footer-section -->
    <section>
        <footer class="footer-section">
            <div class="footer-title">FIND ME</div>
            <div class="social-media-section">
                <div class="background-linkedin">
                    <a class="linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicolaszuccarello/">Linkedin
                    </a>
                </div>
                <p> / </p>
                <div class="background-github">
                    <a class="github" href="https://github.com/nicolaszucca">Github
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </footer>
